    "body" : "<p>My <em>guess</em> is, that the <code>@Value</code> can not cope with &quot;complex&quot; types.  You can go with a prop class like this:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>@Component\n@ConfigurationProperties('ignore')\nclass IgnoreSettings {\n    List&lt;String&gt; filenames\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Please note:</strong> This code is <em>Groovy</em> - <strong>not Java</strong> - to keep the example short!  See the comments for tips how to adopt.</p>\n<p>See the complete example <a href=\"https://github.com/christoph-frick/so-springboot-yaml-string-list\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/christoph-frick/so-springboot-yaml-string-list</a></p>\n"
